The original verifier only checks that /app/report.json exists and is non-empty. An agent could pass by writing any content, for example:

This would incorrectly pass the original verifier:

Shell

echo "hello" > /app/report.json

or

Shell

echo '{"foo":123}' > /app/report.json

Those outputs are non-empty files, so both tests would pass even though the task requirements were not satisfied.
